I am Type 2 Diabetic with 3 amazing kiddos. They are my ùôíùôÉùôî for trying my hardest to reverse this disease. ‚Å£

My aunt (who was like a mom to me) passed away in March this year, from complications of being diabetic. In the last few years of her life she went on dialysis (3x a week), lost her eyesight, and other organs were shutting down. Seeing her slowly be affected by it was such a hard thing to see. ‚Å£
‚Å£
When I was diagnosed in November 2017, I went to her for comfort, advice and so much more. She always encouraged me to control my blood sugar levels and once told me to not make the mistakes she made and to focus hard on reversing it. ‚Å£
‚Å£
Today is National Diabetes Day and I am here to spread awareness about this disease. I will not let it take control of my life and I will fight this!‚Å£
